Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
define_bundled_bus(25.10)                            define_bundled_bus(25.10)

Name
       define_bundled_bus - Allows you to control user-defined bus groups

Syntax
       define_bundled_bus

       [-help]

       [-add_members <string>]

       [-delete_members <string>]

       [-name <string>]

       Allows you to control user-defined bus groups.

       The  software automatically identifies bus nets. However, in some cases
       the software may not be able to mark bus bits properly (or treat marked
       bits as bus). For improved bus identification,  the  define_bundled_bus
       command allows you to control the nets that you want to add (or remove)
       from the list of recognized bus bits.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       -add_members <string>
              Specifies the name of nets to be added to the group.

       -delete_members <string>
              Specifies the name of nets to be deleted from the group.

       -name <string>
              Specifies the name of the group.

Examples
              * The  following  example  command  will create a bus named bus1
                with 3 net members x[1] and x[2]:

                define_bundled_bus -name bus1 -add_members {x[1] x[2]}

                report_bundled_bus -type user_defined

                ###############################################################

                Summary:

                Total number of user defined bus groups reported = 1

                Total number of tool inferred bus groups reported = 0

                ---------------------------------------------------------------

                Group Name (user_defined) : bus1

                Constituents:

                - x[1]

                - x[2]

              * The following example command will add one  more  member  x[3]
                and delete member x[2] to the bus 'bus1':

                define_bundled_bus  -name  bus1 -add_members x[3] -delete_mem-
                bers x[2]

                Added [1] net(s) to group 'bus1'.

                Deleted [1] net(s) from user-defined group 'bus1'.

Related Information
